itemDescription: diver who won bronze medals in the 1m and 3m springboard events at the 2002 Commonwealth Games

wikipedia_page.main: Jane Smith (born 25 November 1975) is an English former diver, who won bronze medals in the 1m and 3m springboard events at the 2002 Commonwealth Games. She also competed for Great Britain at the 2000 and 2004 Summer Olympics. Smith competed for the City of Sheffield diving club.
